<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Razor">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <!-- Allow the deliberate Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions downgrade below (see note on package references). -->
    <NoWarn>$(NoWarn);NU1605</NoWarn>

    <!-- dotnet tool settings -->
    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>
    <ToolCommandName>mandocode</ToolCommandName>
    <PackageId>MandoCode</PackageId>

    <!-- NuGet metadata -->
    <Version>0.9.9</Version>
    <Authors>Armando Fernandez (DevMando)</Authors>
    <Description>Your AI coding assistant — run locally or in the cloud with Ollama. No API keys required. Just you and your code.</Description>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</RepositoryUrl>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageTags>ai;cli;coding-assistant;ollama;semantic-kernel;local-llm</PackageTags>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <PackageIcon>MC.png</PackageIcon>
    <ApplicationIcon>MC.ico</ApplicationIcon>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
v0.9.9 — Onboarding overhaul

First-run is now a guided wizard instead of a static "install Ollama, run serve, pull a model, then come back" panel. The path from `dotnet tool install -g MandoCode` to first chat is auto-detected, auto-recovered, or auto-installed at every step where it's possible.

Added:
- Guided wizard auto-fires on first run and via `/setup`. Walks users through Ollama install → daemon start → cloud sign-in → model pick → context size, all from inside the terminal.
- Auto-install Ollama via `winget` / `brew` / `curl install.sh` with inherited stdio so users see the installer's progress. Falls back to opening ollama.com/download if the install fails.
- Auto-launch `ollama signin` as a child process — browser opens to confirm, CLI writes the local token automatically. No more "browser sign-in alone isn't enough" trap.
- Auto-launch `ollama serve` when the daemon isn't running, with a Spectre Status spinner showing live progress.
- 401 auto-recovery on chat — if the daemon returns 401 mid-session, the cloud sign-in walkthrough fires immediately so users don't have to type `/setup`.
- Trailing-slash heal on the Ollama URL: `http://localhost:11434/` is detected and silently corrected.
- Wrong-port auto-fallback: when the configured URL fails after `ollama serve` succeeds, the wizard auto-probes `http://localhost:11434` and switches if the daemon is reachable there.
- PATH-refresh detection on Windows — checks canonical install paths (`%LOCALAPPDATA%\Programs\Ollama\ollama.exe`) when `where ollama` fails, so post-install detection works without relaunching.
- Tiered local-model picker with hardware guidance (qwen3.5 0.8b / 2b / 4b / 9b with VRAM expectations).
- Cloud upsell: after a local pull, surfaces `minimax-m2.7:cloud` as the more capable option (free with `ollama signin`).
- Combined cloud/local model picker with `(cloud)` / `(local)` badges. Replaces the old two-step "Cloud or Local? → list" flow.
- New `/model` slash command — quick switch model + context size, skips the rest of `/config`.
- New `--doctor` CLI flag — non-interactive preflight that prints .NET version, OS, Ollama CLI/daemon status, models pulled, cloud sign-in state.
- New `&lt;red&gt;` / `&lt;green&gt;` / `&lt;yellow&gt;` / `&lt;cyan&gt;` HTML tag handlers in MarkdownHtmlRenderer for inline color in chat error responses.

UI:
- k-notation labels in the max-tokens picker (`32k`, `128k`, `200k`) instead of raw token numbers, with current value highlighted at top via `← current` marker.
- Educational intro on temperature and max-tokens steps — explains what tokens are, the relationship to the model's context window, and per-tier usage examples.
- VDOM-aware text input for URL entry in `/setup` and `/config` — RazorConsole's `TextInput` instead of Spectre's `TextPrompt` (which dropped keystrokes alongside the live render loop). Pre-filled with current URL ("press Enter to keep current").
- 401 chat errors render the `Error:` header in red and the recommended action in green; backticked `ollama signin` keeps the existing purple inline-code styling.

Changed:
- Default cloud model bumped from `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `minimax-m2.7:cloud` (config defaults, README, `/learn`, system prompt).
- Default `MaxTokens` bumped from 4k → 32k for new installs (existing configs preserved).
- `MaxMaxTokens` lowered from 256k → 200k after testing showed many cloud models hit a practical limit closer to 200k once system prompts and tool definitions are accounted for. Existing configs with 256k saved get clamped on next load.
- `/help` table reorganized with `/setup` and `/model` next to `/config` and disambiguated descriptions.
- 16+ failure messages across the app now consistently point users at `/setup` and/or `/retry`.

Fixed:
- Status-aware model-list fetch with auto-retry — transient `/api/tags` failures no longer misroute users (with pulled models) into the "no models yet" flow.
- Post-pick auth check — pulled cloud models that show in `/api/tags` after sign-out no longer cause the wizard to falsely report "Setup complete" before the chat fails with 401.
- Picked-model validation via `/api/show` before the wizard declares success, surfacing models that listed in `/api/tags` but aren't actually loadable.
    </PackageReleaseNotes>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="HtmlAgilityPack" Version="1.11.72" />
    <PackageReference Include="Markdig" Version="1.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.FileSystemGlobbing" Version="10.0.3" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel" Version="1.72.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.Ollama" Version="1.72.0-alpha" />
    <!-- ModelContextProtocol 1.2.0 was compiled against Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions 10.4.0
         (uses FunctionApprovalRequestContent). That type was removed in 10.4.1 (renamed to
         ToolApprovalRequestContent), so the default NuGet resolution to 10.4.1+ crashes at runtime
         with TypeLoadException. Pin to 10.4.0 until MCP ships a fix. -->
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions" Version="10.4.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI" Version="10.4.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="ModelContextProtocol" Version="1.2.0" NoWarn="NU1605;NU1608" />
    <PackageReference Include="NAudio" Version="2.2.1" />
    <PackageReference Include="RazorConsole.Core" Version="0.5.0-alpha.20260225-7c02f3c" />
    <PackageReference Include="YamlDotNet" Version="16.2.1" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <EmbeddedResource Include="Audio\**\*.mp3" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\..\README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
    <None Include="MC.png" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
